			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2009</a> paper:</span><br><i>Generating Smart Wrapper Libraries for Arbitrary APIs</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/UweJugel.html">Uwe Jugel</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-12107-4_24">10.1007/978-3-642-12107-4_24</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3f.html"><span class="tagM">T3F: API</span></a><ul><li> The focus is generating wrapper libraries around APIs, treating API design/usability as the primary artifact.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4c.html"><span class="tagL">T4C: Vertical Transformation</span></a><ul><li> The approach is model-driven and relies on code generation to produce wrapper libraries/‘dotLings’.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5h.html"><span class="tagL">T5H: Usability</span></a><ul><li> It explicitly targets usability-enhancing patterns to make APIs easier to use.
</li></ul></li></ul>
